          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Israel's controversial legislation</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/israeli-lawmakers-knesset-vote-bill-limit-supreme-court-powers.png" alt="Israeli lawmakers gather at the Knesset plenum to vote on a bill that would limit some Supreme Court powers" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Israeli lawmakers gather at the Knesset plenum to vote on a bill that would limit some Supreme Court powers. Credits: Amir Cohen/Reuters</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The Israeli Knesset (120-member Parliament) approved a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-28-03-2025-h2-2-controversial-judicial-reform-law" target="_blank">controversial judicial reform law</a> granting elected officials more control over judicial appointments. The law passed with 67 votes in favor and one against, while the opposition members boycotted the vote. The opposition has already appealed to the Supreme Court, arguing that the law represents an authoritarian shift under PM Benjamin Netanyahu.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The reform is part of a broader package that sparked widespread protests throughout Israel. Many see this law as an attempt to weaken the judiciary's independence. Justice Minister Yariv Levin, who sponsored the bill, argued it restores a balance of power between the legislative and judicial branches. Levin claims the Supreme Court had overstepped its authority.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Critics say the reforms aim to consolidate power and protect Netanyahu from legal challenges, including corruption charges. Public protests came ahead of the vote, reflecting deep divisions in Israeli society over the future of its democracy.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
