          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>🇫🇷 Emmanuel Macron announces additional military aid for Ukraine</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;"> Macron greeted Volodymyr Zelenskyy in Paris for the “Coalition of the Willing” summit, which focuses on long-term security guarantees for Ukraine. Macron announced another <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-28-03-2025-br1-4-2b-in-military-aid" target="_blank">$2.1B in military aid</a>, including anti-tank missiles, air defense systems, armored vehicles, and drones. Macron discussed the issue of peacekeeping forces, stating that any such force would not engage on the front lines but could be stationed in strategic locations.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">He rejected notions of lifting sanctions on Russia, calling it "far too early." He adds that lifting sanctions would depend on Russia’s commitment to international law. Zelenskyy agrees with this sentiment and calls for stronger sanctions against Moscow. He believes that effective diplomacy must be based on strength.</p>
        </mj-text>
