        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Where is Tigray?</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/Tigray-Region-Ethiopia-Northern-Horn-Africa-Border-Eritrea-Sudan.png" alt="Tigray region, located in the northern part of Ethiopia, in the Horn of Africa, bordering Eritrea to the north and Sudan to the west" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Tigray region, located in the northern part of Ethiopia, in the Horn of Africa, bordering Eritrea to the north and Sudan to the west.</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Tigray is a region in northern Ethiopia. It was historically part of the ancient Aksumite Empire and one of the centers of Ethiopian civilization. Tigrayans have a distinct cultural identity with many cultural overlaps with Eritreans, with whom they share a border. The WHO director, Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus, hails from there.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Tigray was a focal point in the Tigray War (2020–2022), a conflict between the Ethiopian government, allied forces, and the Tigray People's Liberation Front (TPLF). The war ended with tens of thousands of deaths, widespread displacement, famine, and infrastructure destruction. A peace agreement was signed in 2022. However, challenges remain, such as political tensions, food shortages, and reconstruction efforts.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;"> Ethiopian PM Abiy Ahmed has announced plans to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-28-03-2025-f1-6-appoint-a-new-leader" target="_blank">appoint a new leader</a> for Tigray following a power struggle within the TPLF. Tigray’s interim leader, Getachew Reda, has fled the region. Abiy has invited Tigrayans to suggest candidates for the position. Critics warn that the move could undermine self-governance and peace agreements despite efforts to stabilize the region after the civil war.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
